Architecture plan for issues #63-#67

Project baseline
- Product name is alex-1883-test-33.
- Monorepo uses Node ESM workspaces: frontend/ is React + Vite, backend/ is Express.
- Backend serves frontend/dist at / in production and keeps /api/* available for JSON APIs.
- Existing frontend modules already include auth context/client, sign-in flow, profile page, feed page, post card, image composer, follow toggle, like toggle, and comment thread.

Issue order and dependencies
1. #63 replaces the scaffold App with a real React Router app and route table.
2. #64 adds the shared Layout/top bar on top of the router from #63.
3. #65 wraps protected routes using the existing Auth Context and controls unauthenticated redirects.
4. #66 composes the post detail route from existing post, like, comment, and follow modules.
5. #67 performs end-to-end smoke wiring across login, top bar state, posting, feed, likes, and comments.

Frontend module structure
- Keep application routing in frontend/src/App.mjs.
- Add route/page files only when an existing module is not enough; prefer reusing:
  - frontend/src/feed/feed-page.mjs for /feed
  - frontend/src/auth/profile-page.mjs for /profile
  - frontend/src/auth/sign-in-flow.mjs for /auth/callback
  - frontend/src/posts/post-card.mjs plus likes/comments/follows modules for /post/:id
- Add a layout module under frontend/src/layout/ for global navigation shared by all routes.
- Keep CSS alongside each component and import it from the component/module that owns the styles.

Backend/API assumptions
- Do not invent alternate product names or placeholder auth/storage/database behavior.
- PostgreSQL remains the only persistent database; Object Storage remains the only binary storage path.
- Route implementation work should mount existing backend routers into backend/src/app.mjs only when the issue scope calls for it.
- Preserve existing error-envelope behavior and health routes.

Key design decisions
- Use react-router for route ownership and navigation; avoid ad hoc hash routing.
- Protected-route behavior should be declarative and built on the existing AuthProvider state.
- Keep the deployed backend as the single public service: API routes under /api/*, frontend static shell for non-API routes.
- Prefer small composition work over rewrites; most feature pieces already exist and need routing/layout/data wiring.
